# Independent review: slot-0 / TAG_PSRC reframe

I read the cited engine paths and cross-checked against your Phase 11 consult notes. Below is a code-grounded verdict, not a rubber stamp of `.planning/research/SUMMARY.md`.

---

## Claim-by-claim verification

### Claim 1 — “Single root cause: slot-0-only fallback PS”

**Mostly true as the dominant shading blocker; oversimplified as “one bug explains every symptom.”**

**Verified in tree:**

1. **D3D9 PEXE is rejected; `m_d3dPS` stays null**

```748:756:src/engine/client/application/Direct3d11/src/win32/Direct3d11_PixelShaderProgramData.cpp
	// Current pre-compiled D3D9 bytecode case. We CANNOT pass this to
	// CreatePixelShader -- it would E_INVALIDARG. Log the version for
	// the asset-audit trail.
	int const verMajor = static_cast<int>((exe[0] >> 8) & 0xff);
	int const verMinor = static_cast<int>((exe[0] >> 0) & 0xff);
	DEBUG_REPORT_LOG_PRINT(true,
		("Direct3d11_PixelShaderProgramData: '%s' is pre-compiled D3D9 PS %d.%d bytecode -- not consumable by D3D11; m_d3dPS NULL (asset re-author follow-up; Plan 11-06 draw skip)\n",
		pixelShaderProgram.getFileName(), verMajor, verMinor));
```

D3D9 does the opposite — it consumes the same `m_exe`:

```34:35:src/engine/client/application/Direct3d9/src/win32/Direct3d9_PixelShaderProgramData.cpp
			HRESULT const hresult = Direct3d9::getDevice()->CreatePixelShader(pixelShaderProgram.m_exe, &m_pixelShader);
			FATAL_DX_HR("CreatePixelShader failed %s", hresult);
```

2. **Draw path binds dynamic PS when asset PS is null**

```1107:1122:src/engine/client/application/Direct3d11/src/win32/Direct3d11_StateCache.cpp
		if (ms_currentPSData && ms_currentPSData->getPixelShader())
		{
			ctx->PSSetShader(ms_currentPSData->getPixelShader(), nullptr, 0);
		}
		else if (ID3D11PixelShader *fallback = selectFallbackPSForVS(ms_currentVSData))
		{
			// ... reflection-driven fallback-variant selection ...
			ctx->PSSetShader(fallback, nullptr, 0);
		}
```

3. **Fallback generator samples only `t0` / TEXCOORD0 (plus optional COLOR0), not slots 1–7**

```405:472:src/engine/client/application/Direct3d11/src/win32/Direct3d11_PixelShaderProgramData.cpp
		if (texcoord0Index >= 0)
		{
			hlsl += "Texture2D    t : register(t0);\n";
			hlsl += "SamplerState s : register(s0);\n";
            // ...
			hlsl += "    float4 col = t.Sample(s, input.";
			// ...
			hlsl += ";\n";
```

4. **SRVs 1–7 are bound but explicitly not consumed by that PS** (Iter-44E)

```601:605:src/engine/client/application/Direct3d11/src/win32/Direct3d11_StaticShaderData.cpp
	// Still deferred to Phase 12 (real per-asset PS compile): material /
	// textureFactor / textureScroll / alpha-test / stencil / fog / multi-slot
	// SRV/sampler binding (slots 1..7). CODEX Q5 -- the dynamic fallback PS
	// reads only t.Sample(s, input._v0.xy) from register(t0)/register(s0),
```

```711:728:src/engine/client/application/Direct3d11/src/win32/Direct3d11_StaticShaderData.cpp
			// Plan 11-09.15 Iter-44E: extended from slot-0-only to all 8
			// stages. Always unbind absent stages to avoid sticky cross-
			// shader SRV bleed ...
			for (int slotIdx = 0; slotIdx < kMaxStages; ++slotIdx)
			{
				// ... setPixelShaderResource / setPixelShaderSampler ...
```

5. **`TextureOperation` enum exists** (~26 ops) at `ShaderImplementation.h:498–526`, but see architectural caveat below.

**Symptom mapping (Q1):**

| Symptom | Explained by slot-0 PS + missing Pass constants? | Second bug? |
|--------|---------------------------------------------------|-------------|
| Untextured / wrong diffuse | **Yes** (primary) | Wrong SRV0 routing on some UI paths was a separate iter; mostly addressed |
| Gray eyes | **Yes** (multi-stage in asset PS, only t0 sampled) | Pre-44E sticky SRV was a bind bug; bind is fixed, sample is not |
| Minimap square | **Yes** if radar pass is multi-stage PS | Not geometry/scissor alone per your own radar research |
| Missing specular/glow | **Partly** — needs real PS **and** material/textureFactor constants | `Direct3d11_LightManager` is also simplified vs D3D9 |
| Magenta slivers | **Yes** — no TEXCOORD0 → magenta branch (`:506–509`) | — |
| **Eyes through back of head** | **Oversold as same root cause** | **Iter-44A depth wiring is a separate fix already landed** |

The codebase itself disagrees with bundling “eyes through skull” purely into the PS gap:

```665:677:src/engine/client/application/Direct3d11/src/win32/Direct3d11_StaticShaderData.cpp
					// Plan 11-09.15 Iter-44A: per-pass DEPTH state. Mirrors
					// D3D9's RSB/RSM writes for ZENABLE/ZWRITEENABLE/ZFUNC
					// ...
					// causing the "eyes through back-of-head" symptom: the
					// eye/decal pass on the skeletal character expected
					// either Z-disabled or Always-compare to render last over
					// the back-of-head opaque pass, but got LESS_EQUAL with
					// write-all so it depth-failed in the wrong direction.
					Direct3d11_StateCache::setDepthEnable(engPass->m_zEnable);
					Direct3d11_StateCache::setDepthWriteEnable(engPass->m_zWrite);
					Direct3d11_StateCache::setDepthCompareFunc(translateCompare(engPass->m_zCompare));
```

Your later consult (`11-09.15-CODEX-CONSULT-iter44-pipeline-deepdive-RESPONSES.md`) then says depth is correct and gray eyes are PS multi-stage — both can be true: **depth may be fixed while color/compositing is still broken.**

**Verdict on Claim 1:** Treat “null asset PS → slot-0 dynamic PS + no Pass::apply material uploads” as the **primary shading architecture gap**, not a mathematically single bug. Claim 4 items (gamma, half-texel) are genuinely independent. Depth (44A), skeletal stream math, and simplified lighting are **satellite gaps** that can still show up after PS lands.

